# 🤝 Contributing to LEAF — Learning Emotions via Adaptive Feedback

First off, thank you for your interest in contributing to **LEAF** 🌿  
Your contributions help push the boundaries of **emotion-aware reinforcement learning** and make this framework more adaptive, intelligent, and open to the world.

---

## 🧠 About the Project

**LEAF (Learning Emotions via Adaptive Feedback)** is an open-source framework that integrates **emotional modeling** into reinforcement learning agents.  
It aims to explore how emotions such as curiosity, frustration, and confidence can shape adaptive behaviors and decision-making in AI.

---

## 🏷️ Hacktoberfest Notice

🎉 This repository is officially open for **Hacktoberfest 2025**!  
Meaningful pull requests (PRs) will count toward your contributions — whether you’re fixing bugs, improving docs, or building emotional modules.  
Let's grow the emotional intelligence of AI together 🌿

---

## 🚀 How to Contribute

Follow these steps to make your contribution smooth and efficient:

### 1️⃣ Fork the Repository
Click the **Fork** button (top-right corner of the repo) to create your personal copy.

### 2️⃣ Clone Your Fork
```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/LEAF-Learning-Emotions-via-Adaptive-Feedback.git
cd LEAF-Learning-Emotions-via-Adaptive-Feedback